App Service Helpers (ASH) makes it as easy as possible to add data storage and authentication to your mobile app with Microsoft's Azure App Service Platform. ASH was built with the mobile developer in mind, and requires no previous experience with backends as a service (BaaS).

In just four lines of code, you can connect your app to the cloud with online/offline synchronization and automatic conflict resolution. Authenticating users with Facebook, Twitter, Google, Microsoft accounts, Azure AD, and Azure B2C is dead simple as well - just one line of code. ASH even takes care of securely storing access tokens and refreshing them regularly, with no extra effort required from you.

App Service Helpers was developed as a supplemental library to Microsoft's Azure Client SDK. Rather than replacing this library, ASH extends it by lowering the barrier to entry for developers who wish to build cloud-connected mobile apps in C#. If you ever find yourself outgrowing App Service Helpers, you can drop down to a lower level with the Microsoft Azure Client SDK for fine-tuned control or even remove ASH with minimal refactoring.
summary: App Service Helpers makes it as easy as possible to build cloud-connected apps.

description:
DequeNET (pronounced Deck Net) provides a concurrent lock-free deque C# implementation. A deque, or double-ended queue, is a data structure that allows insertion and removal of items on both ends. ConcurrentDeque<T> supports 6 operations in constant time O(1): PushRight, PopRight, PeekRight, PushLeft, PopLeft and PeekLeft.

The library also offers a simpler Deque<T> (not thread safe), implemented as a ring buffer. This implementation allows Pop and Peek operations to run in O(1) time and Push operations in amortized O(1) time.
summary: A concurrent lock-free double ended queue (ConcurrentDeque<T>) and a simpler non-concurrent deque (Deque<T>).

This is a snnipet to connect to some Intelipost webservices and make easier your integration.

Intelipost is a technology & consulting company based in São Paulo, Brazil that offers a Logistics Gateway API and provides SAAS to many e-commerce webshops that are willing to optimize their logistics overall costs.

Intelipost connects your webshop to all main brazilian logistics providers and supports most used ERP solutions.

The main features intelipost offers for your business:
+ Freight comparison using our proprietary algorithm
+ Daily updates of freight costs, delivery time & addresses
+ Custom tracking page of your webshop
+ Automatic Correios refund in case of delays (brazilian postal company)
+ BI Reports
+ And more!
The major benefits:
+ Activate new logistics providers easily
+ Measure the Quality Score of each provider
+ Cost reduction from 5%- 40% in shipping costs p. order
+ Reduce IT dev & maintenance costs
+ And more!
Interested, but still have some doubts?

Access our documentation available at our official technical wiki (https://docs.intelipost.com.br) or at Github (https://github.com/intelipost).

==============================================================================

An example implementation of diagnostic analyzers (Roslyn analyzers) inspired by the book Building Maintainable Software by Joost Visser and others.
summary:
This package contains an example implementation of diagnostic analyzers for Visual Studio 2015 (Roslyn analyzers) inspired by the book Building Maintainable Software by Joost Visser and his colleagues from the Software Improvement Group.

The following guidelines from the book are implemented as diagnostic analyzers:

Write short units of code: limit the length of methods and constructors. (<= 15 LOC)
Write simple units of code: limit the number of branch points per method. (<= 4 branch points)
Keep unit interfaces small by extracting parameters into objects. (<= 4 parameters)
Separate concerns to avoid building large classes. (<= 400 LOC)
This set of analyzers allows you to control compliance of C# code to these guidelines in the IDE, on the build server or other Code Quality Management systems that support diagnostic analyzers.
